It's the express train to death.

26
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:04,058
Okay, everyone.

27
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:07,478
First, we're going to give you
a health checkup here at the hospital.

28
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:08,938
And then… You're here!

29
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:09,981
Evening, Father.

30
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:12,775
-Then we'll let you rest and play.
-Are you okay?

31
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:16,487
So listen to the doctors,
and be good during the checkup.

32
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:18,156
-Hi.
-Hello.

33
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:20,700
-Let's go inside.
-Young-ji!

34
00:03:20,783 --> 00:03:22,285
Just follow the doctor.

35
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:23,953
Se-kyung.

36
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,289
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

37
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,457
Thank you.

38
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,210
I'll get my brother examined.

39
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:31,961
Se-kyung.

40
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:37,884
Please look after Yun-sang.
In-a and I are a bit busy.

41
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:39,719
-Stay in line.
-Okay.

42
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:43,514
This way.

43
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:47,143
No, you have to go inside.

44
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:48,228
-Director Ri.
-Yes?

45
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:53,900
I know you'll do well, but if the parents
or the investigators show up,

46
00:03:53,983 --> 00:03:55,318
please call the base.

47
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:57,487
Their safety comes first.
I'll keep an eye out.

48
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:58,404
Thank you.

49
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:04,077
Things are pretty much wrapped up here.

50
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:09,791
How on earth did those punks
find out so quickly?

51
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:17,715
It doesn't look like you're hurt.

52
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:18,716
Capt. Kang.

53
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:20,593
Come with us.

54
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,221
Bring Private Na Hyeon-jae too.

55
00:04:23,304 --> 00:04:25,932
Also, she's an accomplice,

56
00:04:26,015 --> 00:04:28,393
he's a witness from the scene,
and the shooter--

57
00:04:28,476 --> 00:04:29,310
Excuse me.

58
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:32,355
Can we do this tomorrow?

59
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:34,732
Why do you think
we're here in such a rush?

60
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:39,279
Do you seriously think
they're gonna run away?

61
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:40,947
-Ma'am.
-I mean, you--

62
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:43,408
I'll handle this.

63
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:51,582
Private Na is receiving treatment
right now.

64
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:55,169
And these two civilians
have no involvement in this incident.

65
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:56,087
Well, whatever.

66
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:59,632
You stay here.
Keep an eye on the one who got shot.

67
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,260
You can come alone, then.

68
00:05:03,177 --> 00:05:04,345
I'll wait out front.

69
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:09,684
In-a.

70
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:13,313
I'm sorry.

71
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:23,156
Did you find the gold bars?

72
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,575
What?

73
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:30,079
I can't disclose that to you, Sister.

74
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:31,205
I'll see you later.

75
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:54,854
If Father Baek was still here,
he would've called them and said,

76
00:05:54,937 --> 00:05:58,358
"I heard some of the members
of my church are being investigated."

77
00:05:58,441 --> 00:05:59,692
"Will it take long?"

78
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,990
Just one call would've helped us.

79
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:18,920
Who are you?

80
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:32,975
You.

81
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:34,727
Who are you?

82
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:38,481
Put down the gun, or I'll open fire!

83
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:39,816
Who the hell are you?

84
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:31,367
Na Hyeon-jae?

85
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:33,035
Yes, sir.

86
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:36,080
Where exactly were you hurt?

87
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:43,129
You shot someone.

88
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:46,841
A man involved in the case
was aiming at a civilian--

89
00:07:46,924 --> 00:07:47,925
"Involved"?

90
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:52,513
How did you know he was involved at all?

91
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:54,140
It seemed so, given the situation.

92
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,562
Did your captain order you to shoot?

93
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:00,480
That's not…

94
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:01,564
I see.

95
00:08:02,398 --> 00:08:03,941
So you shot him for no reason.

96
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:23,628
MARTIAL LAW COMMAND, WOONGCHEON
JOINT INVESTIGATION UNIT

97
00:08:23,711 --> 00:08:25,129
The curfew has been lifted.

98
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:29,383
The current time and date
is 5 a.m., September 4th, 2025.

99
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:38,809
Due process?

100
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:42,772
As it was an urgent situation,
it required an ex post facto approval.

101
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:45,900
The circumstances
of child confinement and abuse--

102
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:48,236
So you decided to trespass
onto private property.

103
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:50,154
On top of that, a civilian was shot.

104
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:52,865
In what universe would that be approved?

105
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:57,954
The gravity of the situation
called for an investigation.

106
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:00,039
A report was made by a victim,

107
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:02,625
and Clause Three, Section Two
of the martial law says--

108
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,669
That's not why martial law exists!

109
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:06,462
Capt. Kang.

110
00:09:13,469 --> 00:09:15,638
Reverted to the national treasury.

111
00:09:16,305 --> 00:09:20,685
If one person had that much, there must be
a lot more where that came from.

112
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:23,354
Funds for the escape, I guess?

113
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:27,149
I wonder how much the total cost would be

114
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,819
for a chartered plane,
investment, and settlement.

115
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,572
I did my own calculations.

116
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:38,494
Since it was a pyramid scheme,
I have no idea how many people signed up.

117
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:44,000
But most of those people
must've been scammed, don't you think?

118
00:09:45,293 --> 00:09:46,836
In-seong was so handsome.

119
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:50,047
According to the kids,

120
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:54,510
Capt. Kang brought the military
to the scene and helped Ms. Jin,

121
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,512
which is why they were able to escape.

122
00:09:57,430 --> 00:10:02,226
Since they were kids, In-a's always
been there to help Se-kyung when needed.

123
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:03,144
Right.

124
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:06,480
By the way, is your daughter okay?

125
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:07,398
Yes.

126
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:10,943
I felt like my heart had stopped.

127
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:13,738
But you know how kids are.

128
00:10:13,821 --> 00:10:16,073
They're just playing
as if nothing happened.

129
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,576
Goodness, that's a relief, then.

130
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:22,496
With the way things are now,
you never know what's going to happen.

131
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:23,998
Oh my, careful!

132
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:27,251
Well, even so,

133
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:32,298
who could've guessed that the kids
would do something like that on their own?

134
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:41,515
Anyway, the kids said they saw gold bars.
Have you heard anything from the church?

135
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:45,603
I knew there was a reason
you suddenly volunteered to help.

136
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:46,687
No, it's…

137
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:48,939
Don't get me wrong.

138
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:52,902
The church was burned,
and the extension funds disappeared,

139
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,904
but now there's talk of gold bars, so…

140
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:59,575
Well, Sister Regina seemed curious
about that too.

141
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:00,493
Hey,

142
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:03,913
if we had just one of those gold bars,

143
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:06,374
we could all escape--

144
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,335
Start wiping.

145
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:10,503
-Okay.
-Careful.

146
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,798
How do they manage the gold?

147
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,800
What has the Board of Audit been doing?

148
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:18,803
Where did the gold found
at the training center come from?

149
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:22,431
I'm curious as to how the gold exchange
is viewing this situation.

150
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:23,599
So, usually,

151
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:27,937
gold ETF operators are supposed to have
gold in their actual possession.

152
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,732
They pay a fee and store it
in the vault of a trust bank.

153
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:36,612
This is insurance for any contingencies,
but it's only partially guaranteed. Why?

154
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:40,157
Because no thief would be able
to carry it all out anyway.

155
00:11:40,991 --> 00:11:43,703
It is the responsibility
of the Board of Audit

156
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:47,248
to check if the gold ETF operators
have gold regularly.

157
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:48,791
So how did this happen?

158
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:54,004
All the money that disappeared
from the church was turned into gold,

159
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,257
but I don't find that surprising. Why?

160
00:11:56,340 --> 00:12:00,344
When the stock markets are volatile,
people prefer safe assets like gold.

161
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:01,637
But here's the problem.

162
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:05,891
How on earth did they manage
to amass the massive pile of gold

163
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:08,310
that was found at the training center?

164
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:13,482
Gold is meant to be thoroughly managed
by ETF operators and the gold exchange,

165
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,444
yet a pile of it has just been found.

166
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:18,779
There's only one way to explain all this.

167
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:22,324
That all of this was planned in advance!

168
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,617
Eternal life!

169
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:29,123
This plot was in motion
a year before the asteroid was announced.

170
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:32,293
The gold management regulations
are already a mess.

171
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:34,795
I am deeply concerned

172
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:38,924
about the impact this situation will have
on the global economy in the future!

173
00:12:41,343 --> 00:12:42,887
But don't forget, everyone.

174
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:45,055
I say we're stronger than gold.

175
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:47,933
We're stronger than gold!

176
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:49,685
We're stronger than gold!

177
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:50,811
Eternal life!

178
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:51,979
Eternal life!

179
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,983
When the asteroid hits,
eternal life begins!

180
00:12:56,066 --> 00:12:57,651
Do not doubt.

181
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:01,280
Our future selves are waiting for us.

182
00:13:01,822 --> 00:13:03,491
-Do not doubt.
-Man, what the heck?

183
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:06,660
-A new, inextinguishable sun burns.
-I thought he was onto something.

184
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:10,831
Though the asteroid might end the world

185
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:14,627
Walk toward the center of the light

186
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:18,130
You will find no death or extinction

187
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:21,467
The theory of promise is forever true

188
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:26,597
There's this woman I know.

189
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:29,266
She says she's pregnant.

190
00:13:30,726 --> 00:13:34,563
And she's not sure
whether to keep the baby or not.

191
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:38,442
But if the baby's born now,
it won't make it to its first birthday.

192
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:39,360
Hey.

193
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:42,029
Who is this woman?

194
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:45,032
Is it Se-kyung?

195
00:13:46,742 --> 00:13:48,327
It's not Se-kyung!

196
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,329
It's just

197
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:52,748
someone I know.

198
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:01,799
Meanwhile, here we are
just digging spinach!

199
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:06,762
And some bastards out there
are planning on escaping with gold.

200
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:08,389
Right?

201
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:11,267
I hope the gold bars are
a good sign for the new baby.

202
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:15,688
Those darn gold bars.
I wish I could just have a look at them.

203
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:20,442
Maybe we'll find some if we keep digging.
Is that never going to happen?

204
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:22,111
You're a greedy woman!

205
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:32,288
Se-kyung told me
to get you to sleep before leaving.

206
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:36,333
It's just as you said.

207
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:37,251
What?

208
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:40,671
Every day, I'm learning new sides
of Se-kyung I never knew about.

209
00:14:43,716 --> 00:14:45,801
All the things I didn't know about her.

210
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:52,850
The way you see her is finally changing.

211
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:56,020
She's not just a cheerful girl, you know.

212
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:58,689
I didn't have to know all this.

213
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:00,816
If it wasn't for the end of the world,

214
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:03,736
you wouldn't have found out.

215
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:12,244
In a world like this…

216
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:16,540
do we all just end up becoming fools?

217
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:21,420
Se-kyung, me.

218
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:24,882
All of us.

219
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:26,675
The end of the world…

220
00:15:29,553 --> 00:15:31,138
and the fool.

221
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:51,116
As you may know,

222
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:54,787
I'm a famous media figure

223
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:58,958
who spent many years
hosting an eponymous program

224
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,751
for an influential media outlet.

225
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:05,714
For your migration plan
to progress smoothly,

226
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:08,634
you need to turn
the public's eye elsewhere.

227
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:13,263
If you were to put me to good use…

228
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:15,891
Excuse me, ma'am.

229
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,267
Director? Chairwoman!

230
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:22,731
We don't want anyone's devotion.

231
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:26,151
Devote yourself to your family instead.

232
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:39,289
If they come with you voluntarily,
touched by your devotion,

233
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:41,417
then I'll reconsider.

234
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:46,672
That's not hard at all.
I'll come back with my family!

235
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:47,881
So you approve, right?

236
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,718
There was a slight hiccup,

237
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:55,472
but our migration plan
will go ahead as planned.

238
00:16:56,140 --> 00:17:00,894
After completing payment for the plane,
we will board on the scheduled date.

239
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:03,897
I think you should show us proof.

240
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:09,486
I will give you proof
as long as you make a pledge of secrecy.

241
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:13,157
If this gets out,
the children may be in danger.

242
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:17,828
It could also provoke the public
and lead to a second riot.

243
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,835
-I'll make that pledge.
-Me too!

244
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:26,253
Yes, I pledge too!

245
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:27,254
So do I!

246
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:29,882
We…

247
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:35,137
will be flying
with the leaders and officials

248
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,431
of the shadow cabinet.

249
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:39,933
Here they are.

250
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:41,351
That's…

251
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:43,562
-Right?
-Yes!

252
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,066
Show us too!

253
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:47,983
In other words,

254
00:17:49,068 --> 00:17:51,737
the entire process of our migration plan

255
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:55,741
is top secret
and is being meticulously supervised.

256
00:17:57,868 --> 00:17:59,870
Code blue.

257
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:01,955
