521
00:38:41,569 --> 00:38:43,654
Of course not. We have Ji-eun here.

522
00:38:43,738 --> 00:38:46,657
And Sister Gye Hyang over there
is about to bite the dust…

523
00:38:46,741 --> 00:38:50,828
I mean, since her days are numbered,
she said she wanted to try something new.

524
00:38:50,911 --> 00:38:52,663
But you're going to keep Moira open?

525
00:38:52,747 --> 00:38:55,583
I love coming here
and listening to music once in a while.

526
00:38:56,083 --> 00:38:59,879
Of course, madam!
Of course we'll keep it open.

527
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:03,090
But why isn't Sister Chae-hwan here yet?

528
00:39:04,091 --> 00:39:05,509
Speaking of which,

529
00:39:06,093 --> 00:39:08,846
why isn't our dear In-a here yet?

530
00:39:08,929 --> 00:39:10,514
-Stop it.
-Hey.

531
00:39:10,598 --> 00:39:13,434
Isn't In-a dating anyone these days?

532
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:15,186
-Zip it now!
-But why not?

533
00:39:15,269 --> 00:39:17,855
Hey, Se-kyung! Yun-sang!

534
00:39:17,938 --> 00:39:20,024
Listen, the two of you.

535
00:39:20,107 --> 00:39:22,360
Go to the bishop
and have your nuptial Mass.

536
00:39:22,443 --> 00:39:25,196
-That's right! Yeah!
-Yeah, do it already!

537
00:39:25,279 --> 00:39:27,448
-Do it now!
-Do it now!

538
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:28,949
When will you do it?

539
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:30,368
I'm leaving soon!

540
00:39:30,451 --> 00:39:32,119
Hey, wait.

541
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:36,040
-Take our picture. Do it now.
-Oh my!

542
00:39:36,123 --> 00:39:38,626
-Take our picture. Do it now.
-Me too!

543
00:39:38,709 --> 00:39:39,794
-Go away!
-Hey!

544
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:41,796
-This is our picture.
-Let's take it!

545
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:43,381
Smile and say cheese!

546
00:39:43,464 --> 00:39:46,133
Cheese!

547
00:39:46,217 --> 00:39:47,885
Yeah, this is great.

548
00:39:47,968 --> 00:39:50,805
-Did it come out good? Not yet?
-We have to wait!

549
00:39:50,888 --> 00:39:52,390
Right, next up,

550
00:39:53,724 --> 00:39:55,768
a parting word from Mi-ryeong!

551
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:57,978
I hate you!

552
00:39:58,062 --> 00:40:01,148
All right, then.
We'll hear two words from her!

553
00:40:02,149 --> 00:40:03,567
Go on, say it.

554
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:07,238
This is so embarrassing.

555
00:40:07,738 --> 00:40:08,739
Come on, now.

556
00:40:08,823 --> 00:40:11,992
Please don't cry!

557
00:40:15,913 --> 00:40:18,666
This country is about to go down,

558
00:40:19,166 --> 00:40:22,586
and our end is drawing near anyway,
so why am I doing this?

559
00:40:24,004 --> 00:40:27,842
I guess I just want to do something
I wouldn't usually do.

560
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:29,510
Gee, I don't know!

561
00:40:29,593 --> 00:40:30,428
Come here.

562
00:40:31,846 --> 00:40:33,764
-Hey, why me? What?
-Just…

563
00:40:35,182 --> 00:40:37,017
So, ever since

564
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:41,105
we came to Woongcheon together,

565
00:40:42,690 --> 00:40:45,776
we've been running Wondermart and Moira.

566
00:40:46,277 --> 00:40:50,948
Well, as for Wondermart,
Ji-eun will take good care of it.

567
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:55,578
And I'm sure you'll all keep
cherishing Moira, right?

568
00:40:56,704 --> 00:40:57,538
As for me,

569
00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:02,042
since this man right here says
he'll stay by my side…

570
00:41:03,961 --> 00:41:06,839
I really didn't want to cry.
What's wrong with me?

571
00:41:10,718 --> 00:41:12,386
-I really didn't…
-Don't cry.

572
00:41:15,055 --> 00:41:16,891
-Don't cry!
-Mi-ryeong!

573
00:41:16,974 --> 00:41:19,059
-Don't cry.
-Don't cry!

574
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:22,396
Don't cry.

575
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:25,483
Myeong-ok, come here.

576
00:41:27,485 --> 00:41:29,528
-Let me get a hug from you.
-Yeah.

577
00:41:30,821 --> 00:41:31,655
Oh dear.

578
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:36,160
Don't go! Just don't!

579
00:41:36,243 --> 00:41:37,953
Don't go.

580
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:40,831
Goodness, they're all crying.

581
00:41:40,915 --> 00:41:43,083
-Stay healthy.
-I'm telling you not to go.

582
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:50,090
Hey!

583
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:54,178
Let's take a group picture
for the Woongcheon FCC, okay?

584
00:41:54,261 --> 00:41:56,764
-Come here.
-Let's not cry, okay?

585
00:41:56,847 --> 00:41:58,265
FFC. It's "FFC."

586
00:41:58,349 --> 00:41:59,517
The camera is ready!

587
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:01,352
-FFC.
-Yeah, the F whatever.

588
00:42:01,435 --> 00:42:03,604
-You have to come together.
-Gather around.

589
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:05,439
-Woongcheon FFC.
-Got a war cry?

590
00:42:05,523 --> 00:42:08,359
Fine, then. Forever Woongcheon!

591
00:42:08,442 --> 00:42:11,654
-Woongcheon!
-Woongcheon FFC!

592
00:42:11,737 --> 00:42:15,324
This must be the last picture
we'll take together before we die.

593
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:20,371
Together to the end!

594
00:42:20,454 --> 00:42:27,461
TOGETHER TO THE END!
D-154

595
00:42:48,399 --> 00:42:49,733
You got discharged? Bastard!

596
00:42:49,817 --> 00:42:51,569
Hey, when did you get here?

597
00:42:51,652 --> 00:42:53,237
Wait. Get out of the way.

598
00:43:13,674 --> 00:43:15,509
You haven't eaten, right? Let's eat.

599
00:43:16,427 --> 00:43:17,303
Come here, kid.

600
00:43:17,845 --> 00:43:19,847
Say hi. You'll be working together now.

601
00:43:21,432 --> 00:43:22,266
Sit.

602
00:43:23,767 --> 00:43:24,602
Sit down.

603
00:43:26,353 --> 00:43:28,522
Forget the army chow. Let's eat real food.

604
00:43:29,231 --> 00:43:30,983
You know Manager Jeong's boys, right?

605
00:43:31,483 --> 00:43:32,818
You'll be in charge of them.

606
00:43:33,527 --> 00:43:37,114
You said you'd hook me up with a broker
who would get me to the US.

607
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:41,035
Drink up.

608
00:43:41,869 --> 00:43:43,621
Wait, what are you doing?

609
00:43:43,704 --> 00:43:44,872
Wait just a second!

610
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:56,717
There is no gun.
He doesn't seem like the one.

611
00:43:56,800 --> 00:43:59,219
Why do you keep looking for a gun on me?

612
00:43:59,303 --> 00:44:00,512
This fucking sucks.

613
00:44:06,477 --> 00:44:07,895
-Hyeon-sik.
-Sergeant Park.

614
00:44:07,978 --> 00:44:11,148
Aren't these supposed to be sent
to the Special Missions Unit?

615
00:44:11,231 --> 00:44:12,399
So Ju-yeon.

616
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:15,402
A soldier must do what they're told.
Keep your mouth shut.

617
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:18,030
-See? I told you.
-Hyeon-sik, take this.

618
00:44:19,073 --> 00:44:20,157
God, I'm exhausted.

619
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:24,578
-Did you check that?
-Of course we did.

620
00:44:32,002 --> 00:44:35,756
The ammunition we had hidden there
disappeared without a trace.

621
00:44:36,256 --> 00:44:39,301
It wasn't you, and it wasn't So Ju-yeon.

622
00:44:43,180 --> 00:44:44,264
Sucks for you, eh?

623
00:44:45,265 --> 00:44:46,600
Well, it sucks for me too.

624
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:50,854
Of the boys who played
with the guns, one's dead,

625
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:52,898
one's gone missing,

626
00:44:53,524 --> 00:44:54,983
and one's had a heart attack.

627
00:44:59,780 --> 00:45:02,199
Anyway, be careful.
Things aren't looking good.

628
00:45:03,534 --> 00:45:06,453
For whatever shady stuff they did,
they want us to lay low.

629
00:45:06,954 --> 00:45:08,956
Fuck, we have to make a score somehow.

630
00:45:09,915 --> 00:45:11,333
Hey, call Manager Jeong.

631
00:45:13,585 --> 00:45:14,586
Hey, good job.

632
00:45:15,170 --> 00:45:17,464
-Same food for the late-night snack?
-Yeah.

633
00:45:20,217 --> 00:45:23,011
Hyeon-sik, the food's getting cold.
Hurry up and eat.

634
00:45:26,682 --> 00:45:29,518
Man, you're one hopeless grunt,
wearing that uniform around.

635
00:45:30,102 --> 00:45:32,104
We got big rooms up on the second floor.

636
00:45:32,187 --> 00:45:33,188
Pick one and use it.

637
00:45:51,290 --> 00:45:52,958
You look even uglier without your uniform.

638
00:45:54,209 --> 00:45:55,377
Shut up.

639
00:45:55,461 --> 00:45:56,587
What do you want?

640
00:45:59,131 --> 00:46:00,466
I have to ask you something.

641
00:46:02,050 --> 00:46:04,052
What? If I have a girlfriend?

642
00:46:05,262 --> 00:46:06,680
Snap out of it, dude.

643
00:46:11,101 --> 00:46:11,935
Well…

644
00:46:14,188 --> 00:46:18,358
can you get me a gun
or something like that?

645
00:46:18,442 --> 00:46:21,320
Hey. What are you talking about?

646
00:46:21,403 --> 00:46:22,738
You were a soldier.

647
00:46:24,239 --> 00:46:26,033
I'm sure you didn't leave empty-handed.

648
00:46:26,116 --> 00:46:28,368
Not even the officers
can do stuff like that.

649
00:46:33,165 --> 00:46:33,999
But instead…

650
00:46:38,712 --> 00:46:39,713
Get over here.

651
00:46:44,843 --> 00:46:46,261
What?

652
00:46:51,725 --> 00:46:53,727
Give it some thought, okay?

653
00:47:00,859 --> 00:47:04,071
Where did everyone go?
They didn't even eat their meals.

654
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:07,950
What is that?

655
00:47:10,327 --> 00:47:11,620
Goodness, that little…

656
00:47:40,190 --> 00:47:41,191
Father.

657
00:47:44,111 --> 00:47:44,945
Father.

658
00:47:45,028 --> 00:47:46,280
Father, open…

659
00:47:47,447 --> 00:47:48,782
Father Woo Sung-jae.

660
00:47:52,786 --> 00:47:53,912
-Let me.
-Okay.

661
00:47:58,500 --> 00:47:59,334
Damn!

662
00:47:59,835 --> 00:48:00,752
Hey, Sung-jae!

663
00:48:02,796 --> 00:48:04,548
Fasting won't change anything!

664
00:48:07,968 --> 00:48:11,680
You have new data in your head,
so come out and start utilizing it.

665
00:48:14,433 --> 00:48:15,559
Are you praying again?

666
00:48:16,476 --> 00:48:18,687
Does praying change anything?

667
00:48:21,315 --> 00:48:23,942
Woo Sung-jae, open the door!

668
00:48:25,068 --> 00:48:27,571
We should make a plan together!

669
00:48:32,409 --> 00:48:33,577
Woo Sung-jae!

670
00:48:35,495 --> 00:48:37,372
Open the door, Woo Sung-jae!

671
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:41,251
Sung-jae.

672
00:48:43,086 --> 00:48:44,087
Sung-jae.

673
00:49:18,455 --> 00:49:21,041
We have to find the link.

674
00:49:21,124 --> 00:49:23,877
Like how Father Baek is connected

675
00:49:25,379 --> 00:49:26,922
to those people.

676
00:49:28,799 --> 00:49:31,885
As you know, my hands are tied right now.

677
00:49:32,844 --> 00:49:34,513
If I do anything, I bet…

678
00:49:35,555 --> 00:49:39,643
Just focus on feeding your soldiers.
Yun-sang, let me use your car.

679
00:49:39,726 --> 00:49:41,228
Where are you going?

680
00:49:41,311 --> 00:49:43,397
Yun-sang, I brought the director with me.

681
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:44,606
Dr. Ha.

682
00:49:46,233 --> 00:49:50,070
I heard you came by a few times
but never once visited us.

683
00:49:50,153 --> 00:49:51,571
How could you do that?

684
00:49:52,322 --> 00:49:53,573
Well, I'm sorry.

685
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:55,742
He's not blaming you, okay?

686
00:49:57,577 --> 00:49:59,705
Of course not.
Now's not the time to be nitpicky.

687
00:50:00,789 --> 00:50:01,873
Dr. Ha.

688
00:50:02,708 --> 00:50:05,210
I happened to get my hands on
a bottle of fine liquor.

689
00:50:05,293 --> 00:50:06,962
Using this as an excuse,

690
00:50:07,045 --> 00:50:10,549
I came to you first
to settle any bad feelings.

691
00:50:11,633 --> 00:50:12,467
What do you say?

692
00:50:12,551 --> 00:50:15,053
I'll come visit you at the lab.
Right now, Se-kyung is--

693
00:50:15,137 --> 00:50:17,597
Right, she's welcome to join us too!

694
00:50:17,681 --> 00:50:18,682
Yeah, how about it?

695
00:50:20,058 --> 00:50:21,309
I'm really sorry, sir.

696
00:50:21,393 --> 00:50:23,770
-Yun-sang!
-Dr. Ha!

697
00:50:24,479 --> 00:50:25,313
Is he…

698
00:50:25,397 --> 00:50:27,399
He still doesn't understand the situation.

699
00:50:27,482 --> 00:50:29,901
The kid's too naive, you know.

700
00:50:29,985 --> 00:50:31,903
Yeah, right. He's not naive.

701
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:33,613
Come on!

702
00:50:35,824 --> 00:50:38,076
Se-kyung! Hey!

703
00:50:39,036 --> 00:50:40,078
Kang In-a!

704
00:50:41,496 --> 00:50:42,831
Se-kyung!

705
00:51:12,778 --> 00:51:13,904
This is Ha Yun-sang.

706
00:51:31,755 --> 00:51:32,672
Well…

707
00:51:43,016 --> 00:51:43,850
Mr. Song.

708
00:51:56,363 --> 00:51:57,197
Well…

709
00:52:08,625 --> 00:52:10,627
Here. It's a bulletproof vest.

710
00:52:11,753 --> 00:52:12,754
Put it on first.

711
00:52:14,589 --> 00:52:16,299
I'm going solo this time for real.

712
00:52:18,802 --> 00:52:21,138
What are you saying? Just put it on.

713
00:52:21,221 --> 00:52:23,890
It'll only take a minute.
You don't even have bullets.

714
00:52:25,559 --> 00:52:27,853
Soldiers have a duty to protect civilians.

715
00:52:30,438 --> 00:52:33,275
I'm just going to check
and come right back.

716
00:52:38,655 --> 00:52:39,489
Se-kyung.

717
00:52:40,740 --> 00:52:44,327
Do you believe that finding Father Baek
will lead you to a solution?

718
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:46,913
I wish.

719
00:52:46,997 --> 00:52:49,166
We all saw the video on the dashcam.

720
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:50,667
Father Baek ran away and--

721
00:52:50,750 --> 00:52:52,836
No, he's still here.

722
00:52:55,255 --> 00:52:58,758
Young-ji's little brother saw him
at some kind of country house.

723
00:52:59,926 --> 00:53:00,760
What?

724
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:04,055
I thought there was nothing I could do

725
00:53:04,139 --> 00:53:06,641
after the church had burned
and the money had vanished.

726
00:53:06,725 --> 00:53:07,726
-But--
-Se-kyung.

727
00:53:09,144 --> 00:53:10,729
In the end, we're all going to--

728
00:53:10,812 --> 00:53:12,814
But there are things we can still do now.

729
00:53:12,898 --> 00:53:14,149
If I find him,

730
00:53:16,026 --> 00:53:17,861
I'll beg him if I have to.

731
00:53:17,944 --> 00:53:18,778
Beg him?

732
00:53:21,198 --> 00:53:23,867
To send the remaining kids to a safe zone?

733
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:29,039
You should all join me, then.

734
00:53:29,956 --> 00:53:32,042
Yun-sang, Sung-jae, you.

735
00:53:33,084 --> 00:53:34,252
Everyone.

736
00:53:38,506 --> 00:53:40,008
Me alone won't be enough.

737
00:53:44,471 --> 00:53:47,641
Don't worry. I'm just going to check
and come right back.

738
00:53:51,978 --> 00:53:54,481
At least wear this while I can see you.

739
00:53:54,564 --> 00:53:56,900
It's an older model, so it's a bit heavy.

740
00:53:56,983 --> 00:53:59,527
But it's the least you can do
to reassure me.

741
00:54:00,362 --> 00:54:01,196
Hurry.

742
00:54:01,696 --> 00:54:04,783
I'm really busy right now,
but I'm putting this on for you.

743
00:54:04,866 --> 00:54:05,867
Hey!

744
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:07,619
Waiting won't kill you.

745
00:54:07,702 --> 00:54:09,704
-I put it on.
-But a bullet will.

746
00:54:09,788 --> 00:54:11,623
Or an asteroid will?

747
00:54:12,582 --> 00:54:14,167
Seriously, that mouth of yours.

748
00:54:15,502 --> 00:54:17,462
Don't worry. I'll be back, okay?

749
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:31,017
Don't worry. I'll be right back.

750
00:54:31,101 --> 00:54:33,019
-You promised. Okay?
-Yeah.

751
00:54:33,103 --> 00:54:34,396
Yeah, I promise.

752
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:47,033
You're doing well for yourself.

753
00:54:47,117 --> 00:54:50,453
All the other shops closed down
because they couldn't get the ingredients.

754
00:54:50,537 --> 00:54:52,539
The nightclub managers provide it all.

755
00:54:53,123 --> 00:54:54,874
Where do they get it?

756
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:55,875
Who knows?

757
00:54:56,626 --> 00:55:00,130
Heck, they charge me too much.
I might as well quit doing this.

758
00:55:01,631 --> 00:55:05,552
They say the ration will be increasing,
so at least I won't starve to death.

759
00:55:10,348 --> 00:55:13,893
Do you happen to know the managers here?

760
00:55:14,769 --> 00:55:17,439
Everyone is a manager here.

761
00:55:17,522 --> 00:55:19,691
Manager Lee, Manager Kim.
It's all bullshit.

762
00:55:19,774 --> 00:55:22,777
Well, this guy doesn't work in this area.

763
00:55:22,861 --> 00:55:25,697
He oversees the accounting
for an organization.

764
00:55:26,573 --> 00:55:29,451
And it seems like
he's close to the people here. Wait.

765
00:55:30,076 --> 00:55:31,911
This man is Manager Im.

766
00:55:31,995 --> 00:55:32,996
I heard he died.

767
00:55:34,914 --> 00:55:35,915
So you know him.

768
00:55:36,833 --> 00:55:38,543
Whenever Father Baek visited,

769
00:55:38,626 --> 00:55:41,421
he'd lecture Im
about becoming a better man.

770
00:55:41,504 --> 00:55:43,256
Bae Jong-su, Manager Lee, Manager Im.

771
00:55:43,798 --> 00:55:47,302
I don't get why those nightclub managers
tried to pay him off.

772
00:55:47,385 --> 00:55:48,720
What were they hoping to get?

773
00:55:54,392 --> 00:55:55,226
Sergeant.

774
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:02,025
-Please step out of the car.
-Sir!

775
00:56:03,026 --> 00:56:03,860
Sir.

776
00:56:05,779 --> 00:56:08,198
Well, well. Nice to see you here.

777
00:56:14,204 --> 00:56:15,663
What's going on?

778
